..TEXT:
The protagonist, about to descend into hell, is described,
perhaps surprisingly, since he is in the company of Virgil, as being
alone ('sol uno').  But see ^Convivio~ IV.xxvi.9, where Dante describes
Aeneas, about to begin his descent ^ad inferos~, similarly as being
'alone': '...quando esso Enea sostenette ^solo~ con Sibilla a entrare
ne lo Inferno.'  In Dante's view, it would seem that the condition of a
mortal soul, about to enter the underworld, is one of loneliness, even
though it is accompanied by a shade.  See Hollander, "Le opere di
Virgilio nella ^Commedia~ di Dante," in ^Dante e la "bella scola" della
poesia: Autorit&#914; e sfida poetica~, ed. A. A. Iannucci (Ravenna:
Longo, 1993), p. 256.
