The meaning of the phrase ^alto passo~ is debated.  See
Mazzoni,  ^Saggio di un nuovo commento alla "Divina Commedia":
"Inferno" --Canti I-III~ (Florence: Sansoni, 1967), pp. 180-84, for
documentation.  Mazzoni gives good reasons for accepting a literal
reading, one that makes the ^passo~ correspond to the journey, rather
than, as some have proposed, a metaphorical one, in which the it
signifies the poem.  Mazzoni paraphrases these words with the phrase
'impresa eccezionale' (extraordinary undertaking), while also stressing
the difficulty of that adventure.  Our translation seeks a similar
solution.
