For the importance of the word ^impresa~ in the overall economy
of the poem see Hollander, ^Allegory in Dante's "Commedia"~ (Princeton:
Princeton University Press, 1969), p. 230.  It occurs twice in this
canto (next at ^Inf~. II.47), where it refers to Dante's journey, then
in ^Inf~. XXXII.7, where it refers to the poem that Dante is writing,
and finally in ^Par~. XXXIII.95, where it surely refers to the voyage,
and perhaps to the poem as well.
