|in questo centro~.  Singleton (comm. to ^Inf~. II.83) speaks of
the 'strong pejorative connotation' of Dante's phrase, stemming from
'the well-established view that the earth's position at the center of
the universe is the most ignoble -- because it is farthest from God and
His angels.'  Singleton goes on the cite from a sermon of Fra Giordano
da Rivalto, characterizing the true center of the earth as 'that point
within the earth which is in its midst, as the core is in the midst of
an apple.  We believe that hell is located there, at the true center.'
