For the resonance of III Kings 17:22-24, especially the
phrase 'the word of the Lord in your mouth is truth,' see Luisa
Ferretti Cuomo, "La polisemia delle similitudini nella ^Divina
Commedia~.  Eliseo: un caso esemplare," ^Strumenti critici~ 10 n.s.
(1995), p. 114.  And for the ^vere parole~ of Beatrice, see also the
'veras... voces' that Aeneas would like to exchange with mother Venus,
^Aeneid~ I.409, as noted by Jacoff and Stephany, ^Lectura Dantis
Americana: "Inferno" II~ (Philadelphia: University of Pennsylvania
Press, 1989), pp. 21-22.
